@GekkoNY If $GOOGL wants to build more TPUs, they need $LITE’s for OCS. $LITE needs $AXTI substrates (est. 30% of merchant market, CEO says 40% of InP supply chain). $AXTI needs the chemicals and materials from that happened to be owned by AXT.

$AXTI is the bottom of the entire AI supply chain for photonics since they own 10+ materials companies that produce the high-purity chemicals. 

Basically a materials hedge fund at this point that produces the output substrate, hence why it's has so much control and market share over the critical inp bottleneck.

